💡 Essential New UI Components for TradeX Frontend
Your TradeX frontend (React) needs new pages and components to display the Data Engine's power. Here is a suggested structure:

1. Data Engine Dashboard (/data-engine)
   This is the main landing page for insights.

Market Overview Panel:

A live ticker of latest prices for your 6 assets.

A "Market Sentiment" gauge (from AI insights).

Summary of active trading signals.

AI Insights Feed:

A scrollable list of recent AI-generated insights (e.g., "EURUSD formed Bullish Order Block", "Bearish CHOCH detected").

Each insight card shows: Title, Description, Confidence Score, Timestamp.

2. ICT Analysis Page (/ict)
   Interactive Chart:

Use a library like lightweight-charts or chart.js to plot price data.

Overlay ICT levels: Order Blocks (rectangles), FVGs (shaded areas), BOS/CHOCH labels, and Liquidity Zones.

Allow toggling of different ICT components on/off.

Signal Dashboard:

A table/list of current signals from the Data Engine API.

Columns: Asset, Signal Type (BUY/SELL), Confidence, Timestamp, Reason.

3. Correlation Matrix Page (/correlation)
   Heatmap:

A visual heatmap (using recharts or d3) showing correlations between all assets.

Color scale from red (negative) to green (positive).

Currency Strength Meter:

A bar chart or gauge showing relative strength of USD, EUR, GBP, and Gold.

Highlight the strongest and weakest currencies.

4. Backtesting Page (/backtest)
   Strategy Builder:

A form to select a strategy (e.g., ICT OB Strategy, AI Prediction Strategy).

Select assets, date range, and initial capital.

Results Panel:

Display key metrics: Total Return, Win Rate, Sharpe Ratio, Max Drawdown.

Plot an equity curve (performance chart).

Show a trade list with entry/exit details.

5. Trading Journal Integration (Existing)
   Auto-fill Trade Entry:

When you click a "Trade" button on a signal, it pre-populates the "Add Trade" form in your journal.

Fields: Asset, Entry Price, Direction, Stop Loss, Take Profit.

6. Alert System (New Component)
   Notification Bell:

A bell icon on the navbar that shows real-time alerts.

Alerts for: New Trading Signals, Market Regime Changes, Correlation Breakouts, Data Update Completion.

Clicking an alert navigates to the relevant page.

7. System Status Page (/system)
   Data Pipeline Health:

Show the status of the latest data update (e.g., "Last Update: 2026-07-10 17:00 EST - Success").

Display total candles in the database.

API Key Management (for admin):

Manage your NewsAPI and FRED API keys securely.
